sociorum, ‘ such of the allies as might wish to become citizens of Carthage, he would give them the opportunity.’ So ‘ facio mei potesta- tem,' means, ‘I allow others to have access to me.' Hannibal here is taking upon himself what no Roman general in those days would have dared to promise. But the citizen of Carthage had a very slight amount os practical influence. He had a right to vote or rather to sell his vote in the elections to the Gerusia, or twenty-eight elders; he could vote ‘ aye’ on questions which the Gerusia had decided; but the idea of free ‘ comitia ' was unknown.
